Package cmpt355.project.util

Utility classes that are not specific to the Java compiler but are helpful in building it.
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ConsumerEx<T,​Ex extends Exception>
    A functional interface similar to Consumer that can also throw an exception of a generic type.
    FunctionEx<T,​R,​Ex extends Exception>
    A functional interface similar to Function that can also throw an exception of a generic type.
    PartialOrdering<E>  
    PredicateEx<T,​Ex extends Exception>
    A functional interface similar to Predicate that can also throw an exception of a generic type.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Lists
    A class with static methods helpful for constructing and working with lists.
    Lists.Builder<T>
    A helper class (following the builder pattern) for creating a list.
    Pair<L,​R>
    An immutable container for a pair of values ("left" and "right"), possibly of different data types.
    Trees
    A class providing utility methods related to tree traversal.
